    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="1000" index="3"><![CDATA[~ if we are disabled get out
  doneif (tagis[Helper.SpcDisable] <> 0)

~ get out if we are not actived
  doneif (field[abilActive].value <> 1)

~ gain abilities if we have class level associated with sin
var sin as number
sin = field[usrIndex].value

if (sin = 0) then
~ cleric
  if (#levelcount[Cleric] > 0) then
  ~ increase channel damage by 1
    hero.childfound[xChannel].field[abValue2].value += 1
  endif
elseif (sin = 1) then
~ alchemist
  if (#levelcount[Alchemist] > 0) then
    hero.childfound[cAlcBomb].field[xCount].value += 1
  endif

elseif (sin = 2) then
~ rogue
  if (#levelcount[Rogue] + #levelcount[Ninja] > 0) then
    hero.childfound[cSneakAtt].field[xCount].value += 1
  endif

elseif (sin = 3) then
~ bard
  if (#levelcount[Bard] > 0) then
    hero.childfound[cBrdPInsC].field[xCount].value += 1
    hero.childfound[cBrdPInsM].field[xCount].value += 1
    hero.childfound[cBrdPInsGr].field[xCount].value += 1
    hero.childfound[cBrdPInsHe].field[xCount].value += 1
  endif

elseif (sin = 4) then
~ wizard
  if (#levelcount[Wizard] > 0) then
     foreach pick in hero from BaseSpell
       eachpick.field[abDC].value += 1
     nexteach
  endif

elseif (sin = 5) then
~ fighter
  if (#levelcount[Fighter] > 0) then
    herofield[tBonusHP].value += 2 * hero.tagcount[Hero.HitDice]
  endif

elseif (sin = 6) then
~ ranger
  if (#levelcount[Ranger] > 0) then
    foreach pick in hero from Ability where "FavTaken.? & !Helper.Secondary"
       eachpick.field[abValue].value += 2
    nexteach

  endif

endif]]></eval>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="500"><![CDATA[~ determine number of rounds for frenzy

var rnd as number
rnd = hero.tagcount[Hero.HitDice]

field[trkMax].value = rnd

field[abSumm].text = "Enter frenzy assoicated with a specific sin for " & rnd

if (rnd = 1) then
  field[abSumm].text &= " round."
else
  field[abSumm].text &= " rounds."
endif]]></eval>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="1000" index="2"><![CDATA[~ if we are disabled get out
  doneif (tagis[Helper.SpcDisable] <> 0)

~ get out if we are not actived
  doneif (field[abilActive].value <> 1)

~ increase land speed, +1 bonus on Reflex and attack
  hero.child[Speed].field[tSpeed].value += 10
  hero.child[svRef].field[Bonus].value += 1
  hero.child[Attack].field[Bonus].value += 1]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="rCBNocticu" name="Demon Lord, Nocticula" description="Nocticula is the demon lord of assassins, darkness, and lust, and rules the Abyssal realm of the Midnight Isles, a vast archipelago formed around the murdered remnants of dozens of demon lords and other powerful foes. Having been the first succubus and then having ascended to become a demigoddess, Nocticula now sets her eyes at a greater prize-full divinity. Lamashtu is the only demon lord who has accomplished this task so far, but Nocticula aims to be the second. What kind of deity she might become is anyone's guess-some believe that Nocticula is secretly seeking redemption from her demonic nature. Others say these rumors were seeded by Nocticula herself as a grand lie to distract her enemies from her true goal of becoming an assassin and seducer of gods.\n\nNocticula is certainly mercurial in her personality and attitude. She may simply murder or enslave visitors to her realm, or she may welcome them with open arms-even those who one would think were her enemies. Only a fool accepts her invitation without suspicion, for what the queen of succubi wants may change dramatically from one moment to the next.\n\n{b}Nocticula's Cult{/b}\nNocticula is worshiped by assassins, the lustful, whores, shadow-using creatures, and of course succubi. These worshipers form relatively small cults, often akin to secret societies, that use brothels, nobility, or academies as a cover for their true purposes. A small number of heretics venerate her as well, not as a demigoddess of murder and lust but as one of outcasts, artists, and the glories of midnight. The fact that such heretical clerics are granted spells as surely as the rest of her worshipers has caused not a small amount of discontent among her faithful, which Nocticula seems to enjoy.\n\nNocticula's symbol is a multi-pointed crown wrapped with thorny vines. Her favored weapon is the hand crossbow. She grants access to the domains of Chaos, Charm, Darkness, and Evil, and to the subdomains of Demon, Loss, Lust, and Night." compset="Race" uniqueness="unique">
