  <thing id="raCBVilIdo" name="Idolatry" description="When a vilsteth uses {i}enter image, meld into stone, possess object{/i}, or {i}statue{/i} to assume the appearance of a public or religious monument (either by entering or controlling an existing object or by taking the semblance of one), it can make itself an object of worship and adoration. This functions as {i}sympathy{/i} (DC 25, CL 18th) upon either a single creature within 30 feet or all creatures of the chosen type or alignment within 30 feet. Any creature that fails its saving throw against this effect must attempt an additional DC 25 Will save after spending 24 hours within 30 feet of the object of worship. If the targeted creature fails this second save, it's affected as if under a permanent mind fog effect with respect to the vilsteth. This is a curse effect and cannot be dispelled (although {i}dispel chaos{/i} or {i}dispel evil{/i} can remove this effect, as does {i}break enchantment{/i})." compset="RaceSpec" summary="Can make itself an object of worship or adoration.">
